#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.177"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.177:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.177:0.2"
msgid "18. Sañcetaniyavagga "
msgstr "18. Intention "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.177:0.3"
msgid "177. Rāhulasutta "
msgstr "177. With Rāhula "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.177:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.177:2.1"
msgid "“Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu yā ca bāhirā pathavīdhātu, pathavīdhāturevesā. "
msgstr "“Rāhula, the interior earth element and the exterior earth element are just the earth element. "

msgctxt "an4.177:2.2"
msgid "‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ. "
msgstr "This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "an4.177:2.3"
msgid "Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindati, pathavīdhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti. "
msgstr "When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the earth element, detaching the mind from the earth element. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.165, sc3
msgctxt "an4.177:3.1"
msgid "Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā āpodhātu yā ca bāhirā āpodhātu, āpodhāturevesā. "
msgstr "The interior water element and the exterior water element are just the water element. "

msgctxt "an4.177:3.2"
msgid "‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ. "
msgstr "This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "an4.177:3.3"
msgid "Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā āpodhātuyā nibbindati, āpodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti. "
msgstr "When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the water element, detaching the mind from the water element. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.177:4.1"
msgid "Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā tejodhātu yā ca bāhirā tejodhātu, tejodhāturevesā. "
msgstr "The interior fire element and the exterior fire element are just the fire element. "

msgctxt "an4.177:4.2"
msgid "‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ. "
msgstr "This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "an4.177:4.3"
msgid "Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā tejodhātuyā nibbindati, tejodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti. "
msgstr "When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the fire element, detaching the mind from the fire element. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.177:5.1"
msgid "Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu yā ca bāhirā vāyodhātu, vāyodhāturevesā. "
msgstr "The interior air element and the exterior air element are just the air element. "

msgctxt "an4.177:5.2"
msgid "‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ. "
msgstr "This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

msgctxt "an4.177:5.3"
msgid "Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā vāyodhātuyā nibbindati, vāyodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti. "
msgstr "When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the air element, detaching the mind from the air element. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.177:6.1"
msgid "Yato kho, rāhula, bhikkhu imāsu catūsu dhātūsu nevattānaṃ na attaniyaṃ samanupassati, ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, bhikkhu acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassā”ti. "
msgstr "When a mendicant sees these four elements as neither self nor belonging to self, they’re called a mendicant who has cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending conceit has made an end of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.177:6.2"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

